Create Start Date Filter Instructions 18

1. Drag Class Start Date to Filters
2. Select Next and then Ok




3. Right Click the newly created Class Start Date Filter and select Discrete



4. Put a check for Use All and click OK



5. Right Click the new Filter and select Show Filter




6. Click on the Down arrow and select multi-value drop down list



7. Drag this new Filter to underneath the other filter under the Marks Card


8. Up in the Filters Box. Right Click Year(Class Start Date) and select Add to Context.



9. Do the Same to the other Filter. Add it to Context.



10. Now go down to the very bottom of your screen to the Filters at the very bottom, under the Marks Card.









11. Click the down arrow, on each filter and select All Values in Context







12. Turn on the Filters on all the Worksheets
